// tailwind-prose-coverage.scrml
// SPEC §26.6 end-to-end fixture for the prose utility family.
// Exercises: prose, prose-slate, prose-lg (composition), not-prose opt-out,
// plus diverse descendant elements (h1..h4, p, blockquote, code, pre, table,
// ul, ol, hr, img, a, kbd, figure, figcaption).

<article class="prose prose-slate prose-lg">
    <h1>Typography Plugin Test</>
    <p>This article exercises the <code>prose</> utility family per SPEC §26.6. The container has <code>class="prose prose-slate prose-lg"</> applied, so nested typography should pick up base styling, slate color overrides, and large-size scaling.</>

    <h2>Headings</>
    <p>The <kbd>prose</> family styles <code>h1</> through <code>h4</> with progressive sizes.</>

    <h3>Inline content</>
    <p>Links like <a href="https://example.com">example.com</> render with prose link styling. <strong>Bold text</> uses the heading color. Inline <code>code</> appears in monospace with backtick markers.</>

    <h4>Code blocks</>
    <pre><code>function greet(name) {
  return `Hello, ${name}`;
}</></>

    <h2>Lists</>
    <ul>
        <li>Unordered item one</>
        <li>Unordered item two with <em>emphasis</></>
        <li>Unordered item three</>
    </ul>

    <ol>
        <li>Ordered item one</>
        <li>Ordered item two</>
        <li>Ordered item three</>
    </ol>

    <h2>Blockquotes</>
    <blockquote>
        <p>A quoted passage uses italic styling, a left border in the variant's 200-shade, and the variant's 900-shade for body color.</>
    </blockquote>

    <h2>Tables</>
    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Property</>
                <th>Description</>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>prose</>
                <td>Base nested-typography styling</>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>prose-slate</>
                <td>Slate-tone color overrides</>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>prose-lg</>
                <td>Large size scaling</>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <hr/>

    <h2>Opt-out (not-prose)</>
    <p>The block below is marked <code>not-prose</> and should escape prose styling entirely:</>

    <div class="not-prose">
        <h3>Plain heading inside not-prose</>
        <p>This paragraph uses default browser styling, not prose typography.</>
        <a href="#">A link with no prose styling</>
    </div>

    <h2>Figures</>
    <figure>
        <img src="/example.png" alt="example"/>
        <figcaption>A caption rendered in the prose figcaption style.</>
    </figure>
</article>
